1
00:00:07,167 --> 00:00:11,667
You are like the sea

2
00:00:12,042 --> 00:00:14,999
Every single day

3
00:00:15,709 --> 00:00:18,999
You keep waiting

4
00:00:19,042 --> 00:00:21,500
No matter if I come or not

5
00:00:21,626 --> 00:00:23,999
A sudden gust of wind

6
00:00:24,751 --> 00:00:27,999
Messed up my hairstyle

7
00:00:28,083 --> 00:00:31,792
But it brought us together

8
00:00:31,918 --> 00:00:37,959
Only then did I discover how much I love who I am

9
00:00:39,083 --> 00:00:40,959
Only you

10
00:00:40,999 --> 00:00:43,792
Remind me of myself

11
00:00:44,542 --> 00:00:47,375
The one who used to love smiling

12
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:50,998
Why did I lose my smile?

13
00:00:50,999 --> 00:00:53,584
Unable to find a way out

14
00:00:53,709 --> 00:00:56,751
I stand by the sea, feeling the breeze

15
00:00:56,876 --> 00:00:59,083
Only you

16
00:00:59,209 --> 00:01:05,292
Remind me of myself and what I desire

17
00:01:05,999 --> 00:01:11,334
I've finally learned That after all my overthinking

18
00:01:11,459 --> 00:01:12,584
What I want the most

19
00:01:13,334 --> 00:01:16,999
Is to go to the seaside And feel the breeze with you

20
00:01:26,626 --> 00:01:29,999
"BREEZE BY THE SEA"

21
00:01:32,999 --> 00:01:34,792
She's still not answering.

22
00:01:36,042 --> 00:01:37,310
What if they ran into some bad guys?

23
00:01:37,334 --> 00:01:38,999
No way. Don't say that.

24
00:01:39,542 --> 00:01:40,334
That's right.

25
00:01:40,459 --> 00:01:41,250
Hainuo.

26
00:01:41,375 --> 00:01:42,375
Dawu.

27
00:01:42,626 --> 00:01:44,626
Can you go to Taipei and bring them back?

28
00:02:22,999 --> 00:02:24,719
Are you sure about going to Taipei with me?

29
00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:26,918
There are paparazzi. Sit tight.

30
00:02:35,375 --> 00:02:36,655
Does your grandma know about it?

31
00:02:37,999 --> 00:02:40,167
I just ate with her. She seemed completely clueless.

32
00:02:42,250 --> 00:02:43,626
It's fine.

33
00:02:43,751 --> 00:02:44,999
I'll inform her for you.

34
00:02:54,500 --> 00:02:55,500
Hello, Grandma.

35
00:02:56,125 --> 00:02:59,375
There's something Hainuo might not know how to tell you.

36
00:03:00,083 --> 00:03:01,083
Well...

37
00:03:01,250 --> 00:03:03,918
Nuonuo doesn't know how to tell you.

38
00:03:04,626 --> 00:03:06,959
You asked her to go back with you, right?

39
00:03:07,500 --> 00:03:10,999
However, she's worried about leaving me alone in Kinmen.

40
00:03:11,167 --> 00:03:14,500
Aren't Yueshan and Jingliang in Taipei right now?

41
00:03:15,292 --> 00:03:16,542
That's why I sent Nuonuo

42
00:03:16,667 --> 00:03:18,834
to bring them back.

43
00:03:19,375 --> 00:03:21,542
Maybe she'll get used to it over there.

44
00:03:21,999 --> 00:03:24,083
Who knows? She might change her mind.

45
00:03:25,999 --> 00:03:28,999
Don't worry. I'll be fine here on my own.

46
00:03:29,834 --> 00:03:34,042
After all, I have your "Bros Forever"

47
00:03:34,167 --> 00:03:35,459
to look after me, right?

48
00:03:39,876 --> 00:03:40,876
Got it.

49
00:03:42,083 --> 00:03:43,375
Thank you, Grandma.

50
00:03:43,500 --> 00:03:44,751
Understood.

51
00:03:44,999 --> 00:03:46,792
She can stay there for a while.

52
00:03:47,417 --> 00:03:48,417
You guys just get going.

53
00:03:49,709 --> 00:03:50,709
Don't worry.

54
00:03:51,083 --> 00:03:52,083
I'm here.

55
00:03:52,542 --> 00:03:53,982
I'll take good care of your grandma.

56
00:03:55,584 --> 00:03:57,999
Please look after her.

57
00:04:00,999 --> 00:04:01,999
Bro.

58
00:04:02,334 --> 00:04:03,334
Thank you.

59
00:04:05,584 --> 00:04:06,584
Okay.

60
00:04:06,999 --> 00:04:08,999
It's about time. Shall we go in?

61
00:04:10,959 --> 00:04:12,999
There are paparazzi. Let's go separately.

62
00:04:14,083 --> 00:04:15,250
Got it, stranger.

63
00:04:21,876 --> 00:04:23,792
Hey, your camera looks high-end.

64
00:04:23,918 --> 00:04:24,918
Are you a photographer?

65
00:04:25,918 --> 00:04:26,918
You too, right?

66
00:04:26,999 --> 00:04:27,999
Come on.

67
00:04:28,083 --> 00:04:29,935
- I'll take you to some great spots in Kinmen. - No need.

68
00:04:29,959 --> 00:04:31,393
It's just the three of us, no one else.

69
00:04:31,417 --> 00:04:32,209
No need.

70
00:04:32,334 --> 00:04:33,334
Come on.

71
00:04:57,542 --> 00:04:59,167
- Hello. - Hello?

72
00:04:59,292 --> 00:05:01,083
Why are you answering a stranger's call?

73
00:05:02,792 --> 00:05:03,792
What's up?

74
00:05:03,959 --> 00:05:05,999
Where are you right now?

75
00:05:06,375 --> 00:05:08,083
I'm...

76
00:05:08,999 --> 00:05:12,125
in a corner, far, far away from you.

77
00:05:12,918 --> 00:05:13,918
Well...

78
00:05:15,417 --> 00:05:16,751
I just wanted to tell you

79
00:05:16,876 --> 00:05:18,584
there are even more paparazzi in Taipei.

80
00:05:20,459 --> 00:05:21,459
So?

81
00:05:22,667 --> 00:05:23,792
You don't want me to go?

82
00:05:24,167 --> 00:05:26,542
So it might be a bit tricky to get into the car later.

83
00:05:26,667 --> 00:05:27,947
You should be mentally prepared.

84
00:05:28,918 --> 00:05:29,918
Got it.

85
00:05:32,417 --> 00:05:35,209
Can you help me make a call?

86
00:05:37,167 --> 00:05:38,167
Yueshan.

87
00:05:39,999 --> 00:05:40,999
Yueshan.

88
00:05:42,876 --> 00:05:43,876
Hey.

89
00:05:44,918 --> 00:05:45,918
What?

90
00:05:46,876 --> 00:05:48,250
Don't overthink it.

91
00:05:49,334 --> 00:05:50,918
Maybe your dad just changed jobs.

92
00:05:53,459 --> 00:05:54,709
This place seems far.

93
00:05:55,250 --> 00:05:56,584
We need to figure out the route.

94
00:05:58,667 --> 00:05:59,907
Let's go there some other time.

95
00:06:03,876 --> 00:06:04,876
What are you doing?

96
00:06:05,999 --> 00:06:07,834
Didn't you say not to answer any calls?

97
00:06:09,167 --> 00:06:11,000
But he's my master.

98
00:06:11,125 --> 00:06:12,834
You made that rule!

99
00:06:13,083 --> 00:06:14,334
I didn't answer any calls!

100
00:06:15,167 --> 00:06:17,250
You can't answer it.

101
00:06:18,876 --> 00:06:20,459
Hello, Master!

102
00:06:22,959 --> 00:06:27,500
I'm in Taipei with Tsai Jingliang.

103
00:06:28,292 --> 00:06:29,751
Why did you tell him that?

104
00:06:31,751 --> 00:06:32,751
What now?

105
00:06:33,999 --> 00:06:34,999
Got it.

106
00:06:35,042 --> 00:06:36,042
Understood.

107
00:06:36,459 --> 00:06:37,792
Thank you, Master!

108
00:06:37,918 --> 00:06:38,918
What is it?

109
00:06:39,542 --> 00:06:40,709
What's going on?

110
00:06:40,834 --> 00:06:42,334
Your mood changes way too quickly.

111
00:06:43,834 --> 00:06:45,209
You wouldn't understand, kid.

112
00:06:46,918 --> 00:06:47,999
We're the same age.

113
00:06:48,417 --> 00:06:49,626
- You... - Come with me.

114
00:06:50,626 --> 00:06:51,751
Where are we going?

115
00:06:51,918 --> 00:06:52,999
We got lucky.

116
00:06:53,375 --> 00:06:54,500
Tell me what it is first.

117
00:07:05,999 --> 00:07:06,999
Bai Yinmo.

118
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:08,640
Your mom joined the reality show for you.

119
00:07:08,709 --> 00:07:09,500
Why did you run away?

120
00:07:09,626 --> 00:07:10,975
- Will you quit the entertainment industry? - Please answer.

121
00:07:10,999 --> 00:07:12,599
Will you protest to the production team?

122
00:07:13,709 --> 00:07:14,709
He ran away.

123
00:07:14,999 --> 00:07:16,709
Are you feeling guilty?

124
00:07:17,626 --> 00:07:19,786
Excuse me. I need to pick up two people along the way.

125
00:07:20,999 --> 00:07:21,999
Sure, sir.

126
00:07:24,209 --> 00:07:25,569
Is this your first day on the job?

127
00:07:25,834 --> 00:07:26,626
Yes.

128
00:07:26,751 --> 00:07:28,000
I used to deliver seafood.

129
00:07:28,125 --> 00:07:29,165
Now I deliver sea urchins.

130
00:07:33,626 --> 00:07:34,626
Hello?

131
00:07:34,999 --> 00:07:36,399
Li, will you be heading back today?

132
00:07:36,709 --> 00:07:37,999
We'll probably be back later.

133
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:38,999
Yes.

134
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:41,040
We just got here not long ago. We're still waiting.

135
00:07:45,918 --> 00:07:46,998
Lu, get ready.

136
00:07:46,999 --> 00:07:48,542
Okay. Wait for me.

137
00:08:05,500 --> 00:08:06,500
We've arrived.

138
00:08:12,876 --> 00:08:14,435
- Driver, you can park here. - This is the place.

139
00:08:14,459 --> 00:08:15,999
Xiaoguang will move the car later.

140
00:08:16,083 --> 00:08:17,667
Got it, sir.

141
00:08:22,334 --> 00:08:23,459
Seriously.

142
00:08:25,250 --> 00:08:26,667
Make yourself at home.

143
00:08:28,709 --> 00:08:30,709
Tsai Jingliang, come take a look!

144
00:08:31,375 --> 00:08:33,792
This place is huge.

145
00:08:33,918 --> 00:08:35,292
It's so big.

146
00:08:35,417 --> 00:08:36,999
What's all this stuff on the table?

147
00:08:38,083 --> 00:08:40,000
Is the outside also your house?

148
00:08:40,125 --> 00:08:41,999
Your rooms are on the third floor. Come on.

149
00:08:44,999 --> 00:08:45,999
Driver.

150
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:47,209
Hurry up.

151
00:08:47,334 --> 00:08:49,000
I'm off duty.

152
00:08:50,584 --> 00:08:51,584
It's transparent.

153
00:08:53,292 --> 00:08:54,584
The third floor.

154
00:08:56,876 --> 00:08:57,999
A gym?

155
00:08:58,125 --> 00:09:00,709
- Yinmo, you have a gym. - There are trees.

156
00:09:00,999 --> 00:09:01,999
Jingliang.

157
00:09:02,959 --> 00:09:03,999
This is your room.

158
00:09:04,209 --> 00:09:05,209
You'll sleep here.

159
00:09:05,250 --> 00:09:06,417
It's so beautiful.

160
00:09:06,667 --> 00:09:07,998
This place is amazing.

161
00:09:07,999 --> 00:09:08,999
You two, follow me.

162
00:09:12,209 --> 00:09:13,999
You two will sleep in this room.

163
00:09:16,751 --> 00:09:19,125
It's huge!

164
00:09:20,999 --> 00:09:22,319
I'll go handle some things first.

165
00:09:25,999 --> 00:09:27,167
This is awesome.

166
00:09:39,792 --> 00:09:40,792
Hello, Tang Mi.

167
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:42,292
I just got back to Taipei.

168
00:09:42,417 --> 00:09:44,457
Did you and my mom get harassed when you came back?

169
00:09:44,959 --> 00:09:47,876
When I dropped your mom off, we spotted some paparazzi.

170
00:09:47,999 --> 00:09:49,500
I took her away immediately.

171
00:09:49,626 --> 00:09:51,876
She's staying at a hotel for a few days.

172
00:09:53,167 --> 00:09:54,167
What about Lily?

173
00:09:54,999 --> 00:09:56,479
She still hasn't picked up the phone.

174
00:09:59,792 --> 00:10:00,792
Okay, got it.

175
00:10:01,584 --> 00:10:02,584
Thank you.

176
00:10:12,209 --> 00:10:13,792
Hey, you two.

177
00:10:13,999 --> 00:10:16,584
Don't you ever think about your dad and grandma?

178
00:10:19,375 --> 00:10:21,250
After I left,

179
00:10:22,042 --> 00:10:23,167
did she find me at school?

180
00:10:23,999 --> 00:10:25,751
You finally care about her.

181
00:10:26,918 --> 00:10:27,792
No.

182
00:10:27,918 --> 00:10:29,167
I'm just asking.

183
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:33,042
Well, Hainuo.

184
00:10:34,500 --> 00:10:35,500
My dad...

185
00:10:37,999 --> 00:10:40,584
I didn't answer his calls. Is he really mad?

186
00:10:42,125 --> 00:10:43,375
You two...

187
00:10:44,918 --> 00:10:47,167
They're probably thrilled that you both are gone.

188
00:10:47,792 --> 00:10:50,751
They finally get a break.

189
00:10:50,876 --> 00:10:53,459
So you can stay in Taipei for as long as you like.

190
00:10:53,584 --> 00:10:56,334
They won't be calling to check on you.

191
00:11:01,834 --> 00:11:02,834
No way.

192
00:11:05,334 --> 00:11:08,250
Weren't you always insisting on staying with your dad?

193
00:11:08,375 --> 00:11:10,999
But why did you come to Taipei so abruptly?

194
00:11:13,792 --> 00:11:16,312
I joined the reality show and my grandma wasn't happy about it.

195
00:11:17,876 --> 00:11:19,268
Well, it's not just about the reality show.

196
00:11:19,292 --> 00:11:20,999
No matter what I do, she's never happy.

197
00:11:21,709 --> 00:11:23,250
I'm grown up now.

198
00:11:24,167 --> 00:11:26,250
Besides, coming to Taipei won't trouble my dad.

199
00:11:26,959 --> 00:11:28,079
I can even take care of him.

200
00:11:29,083 --> 00:11:31,542
Plus, it's hard to explain everything over the phone.

201
00:11:32,292 --> 00:11:33,435
A face-to-face conversation is needed

202
00:11:33,459 --> 00:11:35,339
so he can really understand Yueshan's feelings.

203
00:11:37,209 --> 00:11:38,209
What about you?

204
00:11:38,292 --> 00:11:39,334
Why did you come along?

205
00:11:39,459 --> 00:11:40,459
I...

206
00:11:41,334 --> 00:11:42,459
I came to accompany Yueshan.

207
00:11:44,542 --> 00:11:45,542
All right.

208
00:11:45,999 --> 00:11:48,999
Anyway, I finally convinced Ms. Siou'e

209
00:11:50,083 --> 00:11:52,125
to let you stay in Taipei.

210
00:11:53,584 --> 00:11:55,375
However, can you promise me

211
00:11:55,500 --> 00:11:57,042
that once you find your dad,

212
00:11:57,167 --> 00:11:58,607
you'll return to Kinmen immediately?

213
00:12:03,667 --> 00:12:04,667
I promise.

214
00:12:05,999 --> 00:12:06,999
Hainuo.

215
00:12:07,999 --> 00:12:09,667
Yinmo's news has caused quite a stir.

216
00:12:10,417 --> 00:12:12,167
Is it okay for us to bother him?

217
00:12:13,042 --> 00:12:16,125
We'll just stay quiet

218
00:12:16,500 --> 00:12:17,999
and give him some space.

219
00:12:19,709 --> 00:12:20,709
Got it.

220
00:12:23,999 --> 00:12:26,042
You should drive slower.

221
00:12:26,751 --> 00:12:29,709
The bouncing pebbles scratched the paint.

222
00:12:32,918 --> 00:12:34,626
I took Hainuo to the airport today

223
00:12:36,375 --> 00:12:38,042
to fly to Taipei with Bai Yinmo.

224
00:12:43,209 --> 00:12:44,209
It's not bad.

225
00:12:47,334 --> 00:12:48,334
Yes.

226
00:12:49,667 --> 00:12:52,999
The group chat was buzzing all afternoon.

227
00:12:53,626 --> 00:12:56,209
Everyone was talking about looking for the two kids.

228
00:12:58,999 --> 00:13:01,042
What's going on lately?

229
00:13:02,459 --> 00:13:04,500
Bai Yinmo ran away from the reality show

230
00:13:04,999 --> 00:13:07,999
and now the two kids have run away from home.

231
00:13:11,792 --> 00:13:13,542
It feels like

232
00:13:13,999 --> 00:13:15,375
we're all in a great escape.

233
00:13:16,999 --> 00:13:18,000
But you stayed.

234
00:13:20,959 --> 00:13:22,083
Now I finally understand

235
00:13:22,709 --> 00:13:24,509
what it feels like to be the one left behind.

236
00:13:25,083 --> 00:13:26,542
Maybe I'll leave too.

237
00:13:28,334 --> 00:13:31,459
Do you prefer to say a proper goodbye or not say anything at all?

238
00:13:34,250 --> 00:13:37,375
If you leave, who will I talk to every day

239
00:13:37,500 --> 00:13:38,834
about my life updates?

240
00:13:41,542 --> 00:13:42,667
I'll go get some paint.

241
00:14:00,500 --> 00:14:01,500
You guys.

242
00:14:01,999 --> 00:14:02,999
Why are you so quiet?

243
00:14:05,042 --> 00:14:08,751
We saw that you were busy, so we didn't want to disturb you.

244
00:14:08,876 --> 00:14:09,959
I'm done now.

245
00:14:11,459 --> 00:14:12,999
So now you can...

246
00:14:13,792 --> 00:14:15,000
Party!

247
00:14:15,999 --> 00:14:19,000
- I'm hungry! - Let's have hotpot.

248
00:14:19,125 --> 00:14:24,584
Let's eat hotpot.

249
00:14:24,709 --> 00:14:25,999
Who can cook?

250
00:14:26,042 --> 00:14:27,125
I'll do it.

251
00:14:27,542 --> 00:14:29,918
You guys need to help me wash the vegetables though.

252
00:14:29,999 --> 00:14:30,999
Okay.

253
00:14:50,918 --> 00:14:52,417
Hotpot party!

254
00:14:52,999 --> 00:14:54,792
- Yes! - Yes!

255
00:14:55,500 --> 00:14:56,918
Why is there no gas?

256
00:14:57,876 --> 00:14:59,834
Did Xiaoguang forget to pay the gas bill?

257
00:15:02,083 --> 00:15:03,723
- What do we do now? - What do we do now?

258
00:15:39,959 --> 00:15:40,959
Tsai Jingliang.

259
00:15:42,584 --> 00:15:43,792
It looks nice outside.

260
00:15:43,918 --> 00:15:44,999
Let's eat outside.

261
00:15:49,709 --> 00:15:50,999
Won't it be cold outside?

262
00:16:02,999 --> 00:16:05,459
Do you have any paper and pens for drawing?

263
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:07,000
What do you want to draw?

264
00:16:07,292 --> 00:16:08,999
I haven't thought about it yet.

265
00:16:15,417 --> 00:16:16,417
Is this okay?

266
00:16:17,751 --> 00:16:18,999
Isn't this your little notebook?

267
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:20,000
Can I use it?

268
00:16:20,667 --> 00:16:21,667
Sure.

269
00:16:26,417 --> 00:16:27,999
This place really has a great vibe.

270
00:16:29,334 --> 00:16:30,334
Don't think too much.

271
00:16:31,250 --> 00:16:32,959
Take a look at the atmosphere inside.

272
00:16:33,667 --> 00:16:35,999
I didn't want to be a third wheel, so I came out here.

273
00:16:39,999 --> 00:16:40,999
How much longer?

274
00:16:41,999 --> 00:16:42,999
It's almost ready.

275
00:16:43,999 --> 00:16:44,999
How do you know?

276
00:16:49,542 --> 00:16:50,542
Five.

277
00:16:50,999 --> 00:16:51,999
Four.

278
00:16:52,459 --> 00:16:53,459
Three.

279
00:16:53,709 --> 00:16:54,709
Two.

280
00:16:56,876 --> 00:16:58,236
Are you keeping track of the time?

281
00:16:58,999 --> 00:17:00,083
Yes.

282
